# Ecosystem Health Index (EHI) Scoring Rubric

Each of the five EHI pillars is scored out of **20 points**, based on **five core aspects**, each worth up to **4 points**. This structure ensures a consistent, objective, and automatable approach to evaluating ecosystem maturity.

---

## 1. Partner Ecosystem (0–20)

| Aspect                         | Description                                                                                  |
|-------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Public Partner Listings       | Quantity of named partners listed on official website or directories                         |
| Strategic Integrations        | Presence of high-value or deeply integrated partners                                         |
| Co-Marketing Evidence         | Blog posts, webinars, campaigns with partners                                                |
| Marketplace Presence          | Listings on platforms like Salesforce AppExchange, AWS Marketplace                          |
| Integration Hub Depth         | API marketplaces or integration centers (e.g., Zapier, Workato)                              |

---

## 2. Developer Ecosystem (0–20)

| Aspect                         | Description                                                                                  |
|-------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| API & SDK Availability        | Clear, public access to APIs, SDKs, and developer onboarding                                 |
| Developer Portal Quality      | Features such as sandboxes, changelogs, tutorials                                            |
| GitHub Activity               | Stars, forks, commits, contributors, and recent commits                                      |
| Open Source Projects          | Number and impact of open source tools maintained                                            |
| Developer Event Participation | Involvement in hackathons, conferences, meetups                                              |

---

## 3. Customer Ecosystem (0–20)

| Aspect                         | Description                                                                                  |
|-------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Case Studies & Testimonials   | Depth and breadth of real customer stories                                                   |
| Review Site Scores            | Ratings on G2, Capterra, TrustRadius                                                         |
| Community Platforms           | Active user forums, Slack/Discord groups, support portals                                    |
| Referenceable Customers       | Named customers actively promoting product                                                   |
| Retention/Churn Signals       | Indirect signs such as renewal rates, support complaints, or product praise                  |

---

## 4. Employee Ecosystem (0–20)

| Aspect                         | Description                                                                                  |
|-------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Glassdoor Rating              | Average rating and review tone                                                               |
| LinkedIn Headcount Trend      | YoY headcount growth or decline                                                              |
| Hiring Momentum               | Number and seniority of open positions                                                       |
| Employee Advocacy             | Social posting volume by employees                                                           |
| DEI & Engagement Initiatives  | Public DEI statements, ERG groups, awards, or internal culture initiatives                   |

---

## 5. Community Ecosystem (0–20)

| Aspect                         | Description                                                                                  |
|-------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Open Source Ecosystem         | Contributions to external community or ecosystem standards                                   |
| Thought Leadership            | Presence in media, blogs, interviews, keynote talks                                          |
| Standards Participation       | Membership in orgs like W3C, IEEE, ISO                                                       |
| Social Engagement             | Followers + engagement rate on Twitter/X, LinkedIn, YouTube                                 |
| Event Hosting or Sponsorship  | Active role in community events (host, sponsor, organize)                                    |

---

Each company’s **total EHI Score** is the sum of the five pillar scores, ranging from **0 to 100**.

Next step: scripts to automate scoring for each signal using publicly available sources.
